    "body": "Co-author: @Duyi-Wang @billishyahao\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nMORI-EP is a high-performance all-to-all communication kernel for AMD GPUs. For more details, see the [MORI project](https://github.com/ROCm/mori). MORI also provides support for CUDA Graph.  \r\nAMD have deliverd a Large-EP solution based on MORI-EP, more details in [BLOG](https://rocm.blogs.amd.com/software-tools-optimization/wide-ep-deepseek/README.html) and [inferenceMAX](https://inferencemax.semianalysis.com/)\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\nThis PR integrates MORI backend for expert parallelism (EP) all-to-all data communication in MoE models.\r\n\r\n### Key Changes\r\n\r\n1. **MORI Backend Implementation**\r\n   - Added `MoriEPDispatcher` for token dispatch/combine operations using `mori.ops.EpDispatchCombineOp`\r\n   - Added `MoriEPMoE` class integrating with aiter library for expert computation\r\n   - Extended `MoeA2ABackend` enum with `\"mori\"` option\r\n\r\n2. **Model Support**\r\n   - Adapted DeepSeek V2/V3 MoE for MORI backend\r\n   - Updated MoE mixer and dispatcher factory to support MORI\r\n\r\n3. **Configuration**\r\n   - Added `--moe-a2a-backend mori` option\r\n   - Auto-configures `ep_size = tp_size` and `deepep_mode = \"normal\"`\r\n   - Supports FP8 quantization via environment variable\r\n\r\n### Requirements\r\n\r\n- `mori` and `aiter` libraries (mori dependency in SGLang will be introduced in another PR #14626)\r\n- AMD MI300x+ GPUs (gfx942+)\r\n- Constraint: `chunked_prefill_size` ≤ `SGLANG_MORI_NUM_MAX_DISPATCH_TOKENS_PER_RANK` (default: 4096)\r\n\r\n### Environment Variables\r\n\r\n- `SGLANG_MORI_NUM_MAX_DISPATCH_TOKENS_PER_RANK`: Max tokens per rank (default: 4096)\r\n- `SGLANG_MORI_FP8_DISP`: Enable FP8 dispatch (default: False)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\n\r\n### Start Router\r\n```\r\npython -m sglang_router.launch_router \\\r\n  --pd-disaggregation \\\r\n  --mini-lb \\\r\n  --port 8000 \\\r\n  --prefill http://{IP1}:8888 \\\r\n  --decode http://{IP2}:8888\r\n```\r\n  \r\n### Start worker\r\nIFNAME=${IFNAME:-enp81s0f1}\r\nRDMA_IFNAME=${RDMA_IFNAME:-\"ionic_0,ionic_1,ionic_2,ionic_3,ionic_4,ionic_5,ionic_6,ionic_7\"}\r\n\r\n**[Prefill]**\r\n```\r\nexport GLOO_SOCKET_IFNAME=${IFNAME}\r\nexport NCCL_SOCKET_IFNAME=${IFNAME}\r\nexport SGLANG_USE_AITER=1\r\nexport SGLANG_MORI_FP8_DISP=True\r\nexport SGLANG_MORI_NUM_MAX_DISPATCH_TOKENS_PER_RANK=16384\r\n\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n    --model-path /models/DSR1  \\\r\n    --tp-size 8 \\\r\n    --dp-size 8 \\\r\n    --ep-size 8 \\\r\n    --moe-a2a-backend mori \\\r\n    --enable-dp-attention \\\r\n    --decode-log-interval 1 \\\r\n    --host 0.0.0.0 \\\r\n    --port 8888 \\\r\n    --trust-remote-code \\\r\n    --moe-dense-tp-size 1 \\\r\n    --enable-dp-lm-head \\\r\n    --watchdog-timeout 1000000 \\\r\n    --mem-fraction-static 0.8 \\\r\n    --max-running-requests 8 \\\r\n    --chunked-prefill-size 131072 \\\r\n    --cuda-graph-bs $(seq 1 3) \\\r\n    --disable-radix-cache \\\r\n    --ep-dispatch-algorithm fake \\\r\n    --speculative-algorithm EAGLE \\\r\n    --speculative-num-steps 3 \\\r\n    --speculative-eagle-topk 1 \\\r\n    --speculative-num-draft-tokens 4 \\\r\n    --disaggregation-mode prefill \\\r\n    --load-balance-method round_robin \\\r\n    --disaggregation-ib-device ${RDMA_IFNAME}\\\r\n    --kv-cache-dtype fp8_e4m3 \\\r\n    --attention-backend aiter\r\n```\r\n    \r\n**[Decode]**\r\n```\r\nexport GLOO_SOCKET_IFNAME=${IFNAME}\r\nexport NCCL_SOCKET_IFNAME=${IFNAME}\r\nexport SGLANG_USE_AITER=1\r\nexport SGLANG_MORI_FP8_DISP=True\r\nexport SGLANG_MORI_NUM_MAX_DISPATCH_TOKENS_PER_RANK=16384\r\npython3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\r\n    --model-path /models/DSR1  \\\r\n    --tp-size 8 \\\r\n    --dp-size 8 \\\r\n    --ep-size 8 \\\r\n    --moe-a2a-backend mori \\\r\n    --enable-dp-attention \\\r\n    --decode-log-interval 1 \\\r\n    --host 0.0.0.0 \\\r\n    --port 8888 \\\r\n    --trust-remote-code \\\r\n    --moe-dense-tp-size 1 \\\r\n    --enable-dp-lm-head \\\r\n    --watchdog-timeout 1000000 \\\r\n    --mem-fraction-static 0.6 \\\r\n    --max-running-requests 8192 \\\r\n    --chunked-prefill-size 131072 \\\r\n    --cuda-graph-bs $(seq 1 64) \\\r\n    --ep-dispatch-algorithm fake \\\r\n    --disaggregation-mode decode \\\r\n    --prefill-round-robin-balance \\\r\n    --load-balance-method round_robin \\\r\n    --disaggregation-ib-device ${RDMA_IFNAME} \\\r\n    --speculative-algorithm EAGLE \\\r\n    --speculative-num-steps 3 \\\r\n    --speculative-eagle-topk 1 \\\r\n    --speculative-num-draft-tokens 4 \\\r\n    --kv-cache-dtype fp8_e4m3 \\\r\n    --attention-backend aiter\r\n```\r\n\r\n* FP8-Dispatch = False\r\n```\r\nsglang# python3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-questions 2000 --parallel 2000 --port 8000\r\n100%|█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 1319/1319 [01:53<00:00, 11.59it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.947\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 113.981 s\r\nOutput throughput: 1118.429 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\n* FP8-Dispatch = True\r\n```\r\nsglang# python3 benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-questions 2000 --parallel 2000 --port 8000\r\n100%|█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 1319/1319 [01:32<00:00, 14.33it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.953\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 92.182 s\r\nOutput throughput: 1373.825 token/s\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Benchmarking and Profiling\r\n\r\nMore detail about Large-EP solution are in [inferenceMAX](https://inferencemax.semianalysis.com/)\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [x] Format your code according to the [Format code with pre-commit](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#format-code-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests according to the [Run and add unit tests](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#run-and-add-unit-tests).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation according to [Write documentations](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#write-documentations).\r\n- [ ] Provide accuracy and speed benchmark results according to [Test the accuracy](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#test-the-accuracy) and [Benchmark the speed](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#benchmark-the-speed).\r\n- [ ] Follow the SGLang code style [guidance](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#code-style-guidance).\r\n\r\n## Review Process\r\n\r\n1. Ping Merge Oncalls to start the PR flow. See the [PR Merge Process](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/MAINTAINER.md#pull-request-merge-process).\r\n2. Get approvals from [CODEOWNERS](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) and other reviewers.\r\n3. Trigger CI tests with [comments](https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#how-to-trigger-ci-tests) or contact authorized users to do so.\r\n   - `/tag-run-ci-label`, `/rerun-failed-ci`, `/tag-and-rerun-ci`\r\n4. After green CI and required approvals, ask Merge Oncalls to merge.\r\n",
